  "prompt": "What are the best movies one must watch?",
  "response": "Compiling a list of the \"best\" movies can be quite subjective, as it often depends on personal taste and preference. However, there are films that have been critically acclaimed, influential, or have had a significant cultural impact. Here\u2019s a diverse list that spans various genres and eras:\n\n### Classics\n1. **The Godfather (1972)** - Directed by Francis Ford Coppola.\n2. **Casablanca (1942)** - Directed by Michael Curtiz.\n3. **Citizen Kane (1941)** - Directed by Orson Welles.\n4. **Gone with the Wind (1939)** - Directed by Victor Fleming.\n5. **Psycho (1960)** - Directed by Alfred Hitchcock.\n\n### Modern Classics\n6. **Pulp Fiction (1994)** - Directed by Quentin Tarantino.\n7. **Schindler\u2019s List (1993)** - Directed by Steven Spielberg.\n8. **The Shawshank Redemption (1994)** - Directed by Frank Darabont.\n9. **Fight Club (1999)** - Directed by David Fincher.\n10. **Forrest Gump (1994)** - Directed by Robert Zemeckis.\n\n### Science Fiction\n11. **Blade Runner (1982)** - Directed by Ridley Scott.\n12. **The Matrix (1999)** - Directed by the Wachowskis.\n13. **Inception (2010)** - Directed by Christopher Nolan.\n14. **Star Wars: Episode V - The Empire Strikes Back (1980)** - Directed by Irvin Kershner.\n15. **Interstellar (2014)** - Directed by Christopher Nolan.\n\n### Animation\n16. **Spirited Away (2001)** - Directed by Hayao Miyazaki.\n17. **Toy Story (1995)** - Directed by John Lasseter.\n18. **Up (2009)** - Directed by Pete Docter.\n19. **The Lion King (1994)** - Directed by Roger Allers and Rob Minkoff.\n20. **Coco (2017)** - Directed by Lee Unkrich and Adrian Molina.\n\n### Drama\n21. **Amadeus (1984)** - Directed by Milo\u0161 Forman.\n22. **The Green Mile (1999)** - Directed by Frank Darabont.\n23. **A Beautiful Mind (2001)** - Directed by Ron Howard.\n24. **The Godfather Part II (1974)** - Directed by Francis Ford Coppola.\n25. **12 Angry Men (1957)** - Directed by Sidney Lumet.\n\n### Thrillers\n26. **Se7en (1995)** - Directed by David Fincher.\n27. **No Country for Old Men (2007)** - Directed by the Coen Brothers.\n28. **Silence of the Lambs (1991)** - Directed by Jonathan Demme.\n29. **Oldboy (2003)** - Directed by Park Chan-wook.\n30. **Zodiac (2007)** - Directed by David Fincher.\n\n### International Films\n31. **Parasite (2019)** - Directed by Bong Joon-ho.\n32. **Pan\u2019s Labyrinth (2006)** - Directed by Guillermo del Toro.\n33. **Am\u00e9lie (2001)** - Directed by Jean-Pierre Jeunet.\n34. **City of God (2002)** - Directed by Fernando Meirelles and K\u00e1tia Lund.\n35. **La Dolce Vita (1960)** - Directed by Federico Fellini.\n\n### Comedies\n36. **Monty Python and the Holy Grail (1975)** - Directed by Terry Gilliam and Terry Jones.\n37. **Some Like It Hot (1959)** - Directed by Billy Wilder.\n38. **Groundhog Day (1993)** - Directed by Harold Ramis.\n39. **The Big Lebowski (1998)** - Directed by the Coen Brothers.\n40. **Superbad (2007)** - Directed by Greg Mottola.\n\nThese films span different styles and cater to various tastes, ensuring a comprehensive cinematic experience. Enjoy your viewing!",
